“Celebrity culture is burning,” proclaimed a headline in The New York Times, where pop culture critic Amanda Hess examined some of the tone-deaf ways in which Hollywood stars have tried to engage their fans in the stay-at-home era.
With Americans wondering when — and if — life will ever resemble what it looked like just three months ago, do celebrities matter?
“The big guys in Hollywood are going to be shredded to pieces, especially if they continue to post on Instagram, ‘I’m so bored.
So far, the event has escaped the scathing commentary that has accompanied other celebrity forays into pandemic discussion.
Others who have escaped criticism include actor Tom Hanks and singer Pink, both of whom contracted Covid-19.